You need to manually inject the trace context into RabbitMQ message headers on the publisher side and extract it on the consumer side. ASP.NET Core's `ActivitySource` + W3C Propagator handle this:

**Publisher (Service A)** — inject context into headers:

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;
using OpenTelemetry;
using OpenTelemetry.Context.Propagation;

private static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceA.Messaging");
private static readonly TextMapPropagator Propagator = Propagators.DefaultTextMapPropagator;

public void Publish(IModel channel, byte[] body)
{
    using var activity = Source.StartActivity("order.publish", ActivityKind.Producer);
    var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
    props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

    // Inject current trace/span into message headers
    Propagator.Inject(
        new PropagationContext(activity!.Context, Baggage.Current),
        props.Headers,
        (headers, key, value) => headers[key] = value);

    channel.BasicPublish(exchange: "", routingKey: "orders", basicProperties: props, body: body);
}
```

**Consumer (Service B)** — extract context and link the trace:

```csharp
private static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceB.Messaging");
private static readonly TextMapPropagator Propagator = Propagators.DefaultTextMapPropagator;

public void HandleMessage(BasicDeliverEventArgs ea)
{
    // Extract parent context from message headers
    var parentContext = Propagator.Extract(
        default,
        ea.BasicProperties.Headers,
        (headers, key) =>
        {
            if (headers != null && headers.TryGetValue(key, out var val))
                return new[] { Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])val) };
            return Enumerable.Empty<string>();
        });

    Baggage.Current = parentContext.Baggage;

    // This activity becomes a child of the publisher's span
    using var activity = Source.StartActivity(
        "order.process",
        ActivityKind.Consumer,
        parentContext.ActivityContext);

    // ... process message
}
```

**Wire it up in `Program.cs`** (both services):

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("ServiceA.Messaging")   // or ServiceB.Messaging
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

**Why it breaks without this:** RabbitMQ's .NET client doesn't auto-propagate W3C `traceparent`/`tracestate` headers. You must manually inject/extract via `Propagators.DefaultTextMapPropagator`, which writes the standard W3C headers into `IBasicProperties.Headers`. The consumer reads them back to re-parent its `Activity`, stitching the two service traces together.

**Key gotcha:** RabbitMQ stores header values as `byte[]`, hence the `Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])val)` cast on the consumer side.
